key_statement.statement:
Lateral pistillate spikes cylindric, 10–50 × 4–5 mm; pistillate flowers usually
        attached 1–3 mm apart, each perigynium strongly overlapping at least 2 perigynia above;
        perigynia 4.6–9 mm; pistillate scales chestnut-hyaline with

Bract of proximal pistillate spike not usually exceeding inflorescence, 1.5–4.5 mm
        wide; pistillate scales acute to mucronate or with awns much shorter than body of scale;
        perigynia 3.5–5 mm.
